text: Internet has been down in my flat this afternoon... What have I missed?
author: RGTyler

text: UK Political Twitter is just mad today... So much snearing and bad blood aimed at one another. It’s also leaked into the offline world. Some extremely vulgar signs being carried by people with small kids as I was trying to get to my Eurostar at St Pancras today.
author: RGTyler

text: I think it’s naive to believe that #Daesh has been defeated. You may have taken away it’s land, but we know that it still had a deep web presence and cells across the world. It’s totally complacent to say we’ve won.
author: RGTyler

text: The ones I saw at St Pancras whilst I was trying to get to my Eurostar looked pretty vulgar to be honest.
author: RGTyler

text:
I mean sure, have a second referendum but: 
1) You’ll probably get the same result.
2) You’ll just divide the country even more.
3) You’ll piss off the EU even more.
author: RGTyler
